%% Event & queue flow (Phase 4). Authoritative for docs/04-System-Architecture.md §5. Detailed queue design → docs/10-Queue-System.md.
flowchart LR
    api["enrichment-api"] -->|per-record work items\npartition=tenant_id · hash=record-id (idempotent)| intake{{"topic: enrichment-intake"}}
    intake -->|consume at per-(provider,key-pool) budget rate\n(lag = back-pressure + autoscale signal)| workers["execution-engine worker pool"]

    workers -->|success| results{{"topic: enrichment-results"}}
    workers -->|circuit-open / retry-exhausted / poisoned| dlq{{"topic: DLQ (per-stage)"}}
    workers -->|completion| wh{{"topic: webhook-delivery"}}

    results --> billing["billing rollup"]
    results -->|CDC| ch[("ClickHouse analytics")]
    wh -->|idempotent, HMAC-signed| egress(["egress-proxy"]) --> tenanthook["tenant webhook endpoint"]
    wh -->|delivery failure| whretry{{"topic: webhook-retry (jittered backoff, capped)"}}
    whretry --> wh

    dlq --> ops["ops review / replay tool"]
    ops -.->|manual replay (idempotent)| intake

    ch --> learn[["offline-learning jobs"]]
    learn -.->|versioned config: calibrators / reservation values / reliability weights / bandit posteriors| cfg[("config-as-data (Postgres)")]
    cfg -.->|hot copy| redis[("Redis")]

    classDef topic fill:#eef,stroke:#33a;
    classDef sec fill:#fde,stroke:#b00;
    class intake,results,dlq,wh,whretry topic;
    class egress sec;
